<br>
If you look at the currently certified motor list from TRA/NAR the total amount of percentage that will be effected is 56%. 56% of all motors manufactured and certified will no longer be available to flyers without LEUP.  That is a fair share more then 10%. If motor manufactures Like AMW only have motors over 62.5 grams then it could very well force them out of business due to that 100% of their customer basis is over 62.5 grams. Companies like Cesaroni only make 1 motor under/at the 62.5 gram limit. That would (in the USA) give them 99% of their motors no any access to anyone without a LEUP. Which could and would very well take a very big chunk of their business. <br>
<br>
As for even AeroTech, 60% of their motors are over the 62.5 gram limit. This for a company that is already struggling from their devastating fire and continuos hold ups on production could very easily kill their business. Companies like Ellis Mt. are at 100% of effect on 62.5 grams and over as well. Many of the Motor venders such as Magnum, Rocket Silo and such will be hit with at least 90% of their business some of which are already down in sales 30% from previous years before the HSA was even a big subject of effect on us. <br>
<br>
I myself have looked at what we as a club do. We are a Joint TRA and NAR club and for APCP flight more then 65% are over 62.5 grams. The most common motors are H and I class. One of my local vendors Missile Works carries motors. AMW and Cesaroni. The study that he has taken shows that over 90% of his business in state will be affected due to LEUP for Instate purcahases. 90% of the people for him are unable/unwilling to meet the requirements for LEUP and will be forced out of buying motors from him. His inventory based of AMW and Cesaroni only has one motor at or under 62.5 gram which also hurts him at 99%. <br>
<br>
So how are those for supporting numbers. The facts are all there that is why it more then 10% or any other number the BATFE and the DOJ claim. Remember, we are looking at APCP motors, this is one where BP motors don't count.<br>
<br>
Hope this helps<br>
<br>
Conway Stevens<br>
TRA# 9567 L2<br>
Fort Collins, CO.<br>
<br>
